org.mapfish.print.processor.http

Class MapUriProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mapfish.print.processor.AbstractProcessor<ClientHttpFactoryProcessorParam,ClientHttpFactoryProcessorParam>
      • org.mapfish.print.processor.http.AbstractClientHttpRequestFactoryProcessor
        • org.mapfish.print.processor.http.MapUriProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationObject, HttpProcessor<ClientHttpFactoryProcessorParam>, Processor<ClientHttpFactoryProcessorParam,ClientHttpFactoryProcessorParam>

    public final class MapUriProcessor
extends AbstractClientHttpRequestFactoryProcessor

    This processor maps uris submitted to the MfClientHttpRequestFactory to a modified uri as specified by the mapping parameter.

    Example: change the hostname of all requests that are http requests and have the hostname: myhost.com to localhost instead of myhost.com

    
 - !mapUri
   mapping: {(http)://myhost.com(.*) : "$1://localhost$2"}

    Can be applied conditionally using matchers, like in RestrictUrisProcessor (!restrictUris).

    [[examples=http_processors,osm_custom_params]]
